      "message": "Excellent questions! \n\n- Re comment depth: this can be specified in the .clang-format file. It\u0027s currently set to `SpacesBeforeTrailingComments: 2`\n\nWe could set this to 1 and re-run the script and see if it makes fewer diffs or \nnot (hypothetically it could actually generate more diffs). \nDo you think Skia should just set this to 1 permanently, or just as a one-off for this change?\n\n- Re preventing backslides over time: I did some googling and it looks like Clang-Tidy has an option for this. I haven\u0027t tried it yet, but the docs seem like it\u0027s exactly what we\u0027re looking for. https://releases.llvm.org/8.0.0/tools/clang/tools/extra/docs/clang-tidy/checks/google-readability-namespace-comments.html",
